thread.title: Prep Volleyball: Lady Jays come back to beat Bruins in districts
thread.title_full: Prep Volleyball: Lady Jays come back to beat Bruins in districts

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Volleyball: Lady Jays come back to beat Bruins in districts
text:
Share 
TROY — The Jefferson City Lady Jays overcame a loss in the opening game Monday to defeat the Rock Bridge Bruins in the opening round of the Class 4 District 9 volleyball tournament. 
Second-seeded Jefferson City won the match 22-25, 25-16, 25-20 to advance to today’s semifinal against third-seeded Battle at 6 p.m. Battle (17-11-1) defeated Hickman in three games Monday to advance in the seven-team tournament. 
Janice Steacy finished with 19 assists for the Lady Jays (13-18-1), while Bailey Diehl chipped in 11. 
Cameryn Campbell totaled 16 digs, while Megan Bleidistel finished with eight. 
Baylee Rozier led Jefferson City with 19 service points, including four aces, while Bleidistel had 18 points and Diehl finished with 10. 
Mary Wehmeyer paced the team with 11 kills, while Tatum Gaines had seven and Rozier had six. Corrin Lepper, Maddi Stone and Gaines all had two digs. 
Sedalia Smith-Cotton, the top seed which received a first-round bye, will take on Troy in the other semifinal at 5 p.m. 
Troy swept Hannibal in two games in its opener, winning 25-14, 25-20. 
The title match is slated for a 7 p.m. start. 
Prep Football 
Jays frosh end year 
KANSAS CITY — The Jefferson City High School freshman football team’s season came to an end Monday with a 20-14 loss to Rockhurst. 
Cortez Burton scored on a 73-yard run and ran in a 2-point conversion. Noah Jahr scored on a 4-yard run. 
The Jays end the year with a 5-3 record. ﻿
